The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 2: Moser Baer India will raise up to $150 million through debt and equity to fund the companys expansion plans. The board of directors also announced an issue of bonus shares in the ratio of 1:2 by capitalising a part of its reserves. The companys optical media business has reverted to profitability and the new businesses have taken off, Moser Baer India CMD Deepak Puri said. Moser Baer is evaluating opportunities and special projects which can be highly value accretive.

 New Delhi, May 2: Market regulator Sebi will issue guidelines on short-selling in two to three months . This will enable institutional investors to sell stocks without owning them. 

 New Delhi, May 2: A parliamentary committee has asked the government to make it mandatory for foreign banks to lend to the agriculture sector and weaker sections of society as part of the priority sector lending target.

 New Delhi, May 2: Wal-Mart Stores has said it is close to finalising an agreement with Bharti for a wholesale cash-and-carry venture and will open the first store next year.

 London, May 2: AngloDutch steel maker Corus has offered to buy back bonds worth 800 million euros (over Rs 4,400 crore). 

 Mumbai, May 2: All stock markets remained closed today on account of Buddha Purnima.




